In September 2013, Santander Brazil, Brazil’s third largest privately owned bank with more than 28 million customers, joined the Business Call to Action with an initiative designed to scale-up its microcredit offerings and financial education services for micro-entrepreneurs. In this video, Carlos Nomoto, Santander Brazil’s director of sustainability shares the insights about the inspiration behind the initiative and company’s commitment to inclusive business. Launched at the United Nations, the Business Call to Action is a global alliance hosted by the United Nations Development Programme Headquarters in New York. Follow: @BCtAInitiativeCopy on this page is provided by Business Call to Action, supporter of the role of business in development hub